now there are 5 nodes but i want to schedule on 3 nodes?

Step 1: Label the 3 nodes you want

kubectl label nodes node1 env=prod
kubectl label nodes node2 env=prod
kubectl label nodes node3 env=prod

Step 2: Update DaemonSet YAML

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: DaemonSet
metadata:
  name: my-daemonset
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: my-daemon
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: my-daemon
    spec:
      nodeSelector:
        env: prod
      containers:
      - name: my-container
        image: nginx

🎯 What happens now?

        Node1 (env=prod) → Pod ✅
        Node2 (env=prod) → Pod ✅
        Node3 (env=prod) → Pod ✅
        Node4            → ❌ No pod
        Node5            → ❌ No pod


👉 Only 3 nodes will run pods


🔥 Alternative (more flexible): Node Affinity

If you want more control:

affinity:
  nodeAffinity:
    requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
      nodeSelectorTerms:
      - matchExpressions:
        - key: env
          operator: In
          values:
          - prod

🧠 Key takeaway
DaemonSet = runs on all eligible nodes
You control “eligible” using:
nodeSelector ✅ (simple)
nodeAffinity ✅ (advanced)

why not on deployment?


With a Deployment:

You control number of pods (replicas)
❌ You don’t control exact node placement precisely


Even if you set:

replicas: 3

👉 Kubernetes may schedule:

Node1 → 2 pods
Node2 → 1 pod
Node3 → 0 pod

❌ Not guaranteed 1 pod per node
❌ Not guaranteed only those 3 nodes unless constrained

Node Affinity Types
There are 2 main types (and a 3rd upcoming type):

1. requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution
Hard rule — Pod must be placed on a matching node. If no node matches, pod stays Pending.

affinity:
  nodeAffinity:
    requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
      nodeSelectorTerms:
      - matchExpressions:
        - key: disktype
          operator: In
          values:
          - ssd


required → strict, non-negotiable
IgnoredDuringExecution → if node label changes after pod is running, pod is NOT evicted

2. preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution
Soft rule — Scheduler tries to place pod on matching node, but if none found, places it anywhere.

affinity:
  nodeAffinity:
    preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
    - weight: 80          # Higher weight = higher preference (1–100)
      preference:
        matchExpressions:
        - key: zone
          operator: In
          values:
          - us-east-1a

preferred → best-effort, never blocks scheduling
IgnoredDuringExecution → label changes after scheduling are ignored
weight — multiple preferred rules are scored; highest total wins

